A federal high court sitting in Lagos, has turned down an application by Western Lotto to okay a secret agreement between it and National Lottery Regulatory Commission (NLRC) over the control of Ghana Lotto Games. In Suit no. FHC/L/CS/2321/19 between Western Lotto and the regulatory agency, Justice C. J. Aneke  after considering various pending applications of the defendant in the matter decline the application of Western Lotto to recognise and give consent to their purported agreement with National Lotteries Regulatory Commission. The court said since there is a subsisting appeal on the matter and the record of appeal has been compiled, it could not give consent to the purported agreement. The case has been adjourned indefinitely. Western Lotto had sought to totally discontinue the case in order to file a new one which would have allowed the court to consider its consent judgment motion but failed. 